<br>
All that time was not wasted, but it could have been better spent leveling, learning, making friends, etc.  With my years of EQ experience, I'd just like to save everyone (who wishes to get any/all their toons an epic) some time.  Epics were outdated with the release of the Velious Expansion.   Unless SoE plans to upgrade them somehow, which I doubt they will, when you hit level 65 and amass some AAs - your epic will end up in a bag or in the bank.  The only reasons Guber and Rokmoss still use their epics are b/c Guber is now poor and therefore waiting to loot Ssra Temple drops and Rokmoss is semi-retired.<br>
<br>
Take a minute to search out some higher end gear on EQ.  You will find that with a few more levels and some quality raiding exp, you can have much better.  (Hell, even middle of the road gear is better than most epics now.)  Meanwhile, you can have fun playing and grinding with guildmates and others.<br>
<br>
Guber <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub39.ezboard.com/bsonsofkings26528.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slimeynotcreepy>slimey not creepy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(2/15/04 11:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p079.ezboard.com/fsonsofkings26528frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few words about epics</span><hr size=1> I agree with what rokmoss said for most epics, however i feel that if people want to get there epics and they should get them. Also for us cleric's its all about the clickly res, with one on our failed pon maze raid we might have won with clicky rez.  I plan on still trying for mine.  But by all means, check out the available planer gear.<br>
