<br>
The quest in itself may be what does it for you.  Really wanting the item may be another.  But, to do epics take friendships and people to help.  If you have chosen to do your epic, I recommend doing as much research as possible on it.  That way you don't gather 40 of your cloests friends to camp a green mob in the ferrot when you may only need one other person.<br>
<br>
Also there may be days or times when you wish to accomplish part of your epic.  If there are enough people on and willing to do it, chances are it will happen.  However, sometimes schedules conflict.  If you really want your epic, be patient and work toward it.  Just remember having a family style guild is both benifical and not for raiding.<br>
<br>
Being that raids are not mandatory cuts both ways.  you can't save up points to call a raid and make everyone on line have to go.  However, the friendships formed with your guildmates is really the collateral that gets help on epics.  Personally, I would like to see everyone who wants to do their epic get their epic.  But that must be balanced with other things the guild is doing, such as flaggings, other raids for gear or just plain old grinding, tradeskilling or ldoning. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub39.ezboard.com/bsonsofkings26528.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xaanru>xaanru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 349<br> <font color=#000000>(2/17/04 4:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p079.ezboard.com/fsonsofkings26528frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Balance</span><hr size=1> To me epics fall into 4 categories:<br>
<br>
1) the ones you NEED, for the good of the guild. <br>
Cleric - clicky rez<br>
<br>
2) The ones that are relatively easy to get<br>
Rogue - way easy to do<br>
Druid - fairly easy to do, unique dot that stacks with everything.<br>
Ranger - Swiftwind, easy and uber haste.<br>
Shaman - bit harder, but still worth the effort.<br>
Monk - relatively easy to get. nice effect<br>
<br>
3) ones that are harder to get, but have real nice effects<br>
Wizard<br>
Enchanter<br>
Mage<br>
necro?<br>
<br>
4) the ones that are relatively hard to get, and are outdamaged by common (teir 3 PoP or revamped zone drops like windblade, heavy windrider's lance, copper hammer of striking etc.)<br>
SK<br>
Pally<br>
Warrior<br>
Ranger (earthcaller)<br>
<br>
then of course the nebulous category of, I have no idea how hard or useful they are:<br>
Beastlord<br>
Berserker<br>
<br>
